review_blob: Nice pink hue, unfiltered cloudiness. Aroma of fresh raspberries. Pleasant flavor with a mild palate.
Im not much for fruity beers but this literally tasted like you are biting into a fresh peach. Not too sweet and still maintains wheat beer characteristics.
beer_name: R.J. Rockers Son of a Peach Wheat Ale

review_blob: I had this on tap at Eli Cannon's in Middletown.  It appeared a very dark black, but was lighter up close.  The head was too thin and didn't stick around.  The taste was excellent with (obviously) strong hints of chocolate and some coffee.  It had some bitterness and finished smooth.
Very good bitter.  the appearance and aroma were wonderful.  The flavor was a bit hoppy.  Finished nice.
Nice copper color, but the head dissipates too quickly.  Nice aroma and biting, hoppy flavor.  The palate can be too bitter.  Overall a decent PA.

I had this on tap.  The dark black body is well contrasted by the rich creamy head.  There was little aroma, but the flavor was wonderfully rich.  It had little hopiness and was very smooth.  The palate was also very pleasant.  A very good beer.
Definately the best beer from AB.  It's sufficiently dark and has a nice flavor.  The head doesn't hang in long enough, but it is worth the effort.

This classic is best enjoyed at your local public house.  The crisp taste may surprise you at first, but it finishes easy.  A first time drinker of this stout may find it "helpful" to dive past the head and get right to the coffee flavored sweetness below.
Call me a history fan, but coming from the oldest operating brewery in the U.S., this is a pretty ggod beer.  I just wish I didn't have to drive to New York to get it!
Not bad for this class of beer.  Enjoyed the flavor.
Looks nice.  Sweet aroma.  Tastes good on the palate, but the aftertaste caught me off guard.
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Organic / Old Brewery Pale Ale

review_blob: As far as ciders go, Woodchuck is the best and this is their most satisfying.  Excelent flavor w/ a pleasant aftertaste.  Excellent choice for a hot summer barbeque.
